<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,327,642]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,435,462]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species was previously recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[852,998,436,462]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dawah, H. A. &amp; Abdullah, M. A." box="[1042,1347,436,463]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="182 - 192" refId="ref27734" refString="Dawah, H. A. &amp; Abdullah, M. A. (2006) New records of Chloropidae (Diptera) from Southwest Saudi Arabia with some biological information, world-wide geographical distribution and taxonomic features. Saudi Journal of Biological Science 13 (1), 182 - 192." type="journal article" year="2006">Dawah &amp; Abdullah (2006)</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="El-Hawagry, M. S. &amp; Abdel-Dayem, M. S. &amp; El-Sonbati, S. A. &amp; Al-Dhafer, H. M." pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1499 - 1530" refId="ref28318" refString="El-Hawagry, M. S., Abdel-Dayem, M. S., El-Sonbati, S. A. &amp; Al-Dhafer, H. M. (2017) A preliminary account of the fly fauna in Garf Raydah, Nature Reserve, Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, with new records and biogeographical remarks (Diptera: Insecta). Journal of Natural History, 51 (25 - 26), 1499 - 1530." type="journal article" year="2017">
El-Hawagry 
<emphasis box="[229,280,472,498]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al</emphasis>
. (2017)
</bibRefCitation>
. It was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[639,712,473,499]" name="Kenya" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Kenya</collectingCountry>
and is further recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1048,1146,472,498]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1158,1242,472,498]" name="Liberia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Liberia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1254,1325,472,498]" name="Oman" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Oman</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1338,1433,472,498]" name="Rwanda" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Rwanda</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,255,508,534]" name="Tanzania" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[266,328,508,534]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Zaire</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[339,427,508,534]" name="Zambia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Zambia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[438,561,508,534]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[572,659,508,534]" name="Uganda" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Uganda</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[713,791,509,535]" name="Yemen" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Yemen</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sabrosky, C. W." box="[805,975,508,534]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="695 - 712" refId="ref29948" refString="Sabrosky, C. W. (1980) Family Chloropidae. In: Crosskey, R. W. (editor). Catalogue of the Diptera of the Afrotropical Region, pp. 695 - 712. British Museum (Natural History), London. 1437 pp." type="book chapter" year="1980">Sabrosky 1980</bibRefCitation>
) (NMWC collection).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,327,642]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,543,570]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Biology.</emphasis>
Species of 
<taxonomicName box="[429,561,544,570]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Elachiptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[429,561,544,570]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Elachiptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are secondary shoots attackers of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barnhart" authorityYear="1895" baseAuthorityName="R.Br." box="[953,1048,545,571]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
, gymnosperm cones and decaying vegetable matter. In 
<collectingCountry box="[386,481,580,606]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
this species has been reared from shoots of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Zucc.)" baseAuthorityName="Zucc." box="[994,1239,580,606]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Eragrostis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tef">
<emphasis box="[994,1149,580,606]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Eragrostis tef</emphasis>
(Zucc.)
</taxonomicName>
(Deeming &amp; Al- Dhafer 2012).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
